Mixed emotions... If it substantially helps manage the war on drugs then so be it, evidence however suggests that not to be the case... On the other hand the wholesale delivery of such large volumes of what should be private data on a whim show just how lax our privacy laws are. You can clearly see the whole data privacy is heavily weighted toward private companies having no rights to use any data for any reason while government has unrestricted authority and power to demand consume and use/misuse that data anytime anywhere and for any reason...
